<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 3:50PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Madison
County through 430 PM MDT...
At 349 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Virginia City, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Ennis, Pony, Norris, Jeffers and Mcallister.
This includes Highway 287 between mile markers 46 and 72.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
